<p>Choosing the wrong CMS costs more than money. It costs rankings, speed, and months of migration work if you switch later.</p>
<p>WordPress powers <a href="https://w3techs.com/technologies/details/cm-wordpress">42.5% of all websites</a>. Webflow powers under 1%. Yet among the world's top 1,000 highest-traffic sites, Webflow's share jumps to 4.2%. That gap tells a story worth examining.</p>
<p>This is the WordPress vs Webflow SEO comparison built on real performance data, not opinions. We break down speed benchmarks, technical SEO capabilities, schema support, security, content scalability, and total cost of ownership.</p>
<p>We have published 3,500+ SEO articles across 70+ industries on both WordPress and Webflow sites. This comparison comes from operational experience, not spec sheets.</p>
<p>Here is what you will learn:</p>
<ul>
